Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.71,0:01:25.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球 象颗太阳系里闪烁的蓝宝石 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth, shimmers like a sapphire jewel in our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.72,0:01:31.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们每天四处奔波 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We go about our days,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.82,0:01:36.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有意识到 在遥远的太空里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unaware that, in the far reaches of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.42,0:01:40.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,麻烦会挡住我们的路 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trouble could be headed our way.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.27,0:01:59.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太阳系很大程度象个游乐园 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our solar system is a lot like an amusement park.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.12,0:02:03.68,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球和大多数的行星按照预定的轨道围绕太阳运行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth and most of the other objects carve predictable paths around the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.53,0:02:06.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通常 一切风平浪静 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Normally everything is calm and smooth,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.11,0:02:10.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有时会混乱激烈 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but at times things get chaotic and violent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.39,0:02:20.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球会被太空石块撞击 被致命的太空气象攻击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth can be slammed by space rocks, zapped by deadly space weather,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.56,0:02:22.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,被宇宙物体的能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}jolted, jostled and threatened
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.54,0:02:25.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,摇动 挤压和威胁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the object's energy and forces of the cosmic.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:30.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球骑在宇宙兴奋的马背上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is on a cosmic thrill ride,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.59,0:02:33.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经常笼罩在极端危险之中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that often involves extreme danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.60,0:02:37.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当我们按照预定的轨道快速移动的时候 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When you're moving fast in on a pre-determined path,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.44,0:02:40.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,希望没有东西横过 是因为你无法做什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you hope nothing crosses, because there's nothing you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.80,0:02:45.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尼加拉瓜边界沿着右下方…\NNicaraguan border is right down along…
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.97,0:02:49.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,前宇航员拉塞尔·施威卡特掌握着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Former astronaut Rusty Schweickart knows first hand
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.33,0:02:51.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,天上的物体会造成什么的第一手情况 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how dangerous celestial objects can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.27,0:02:58.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1969年他操纵过阿波罗9号的登月舱 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1969 he piloted the lunar module during the Apollo 9 mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.84,0:03:03.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在施威卡特准备更多的宇宙航行 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now Schweickart is ready for more than a cruise to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.89,0:03:07.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他发出过一颗特别的小行星的威胁的警报 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's sounding alarms about the dangers of one particular asteroid,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.84,0:03:09.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星名叫阿波菲斯 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}named Apophis,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.65,0:03:12.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2004年太靠近地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which got too close for comfort in 2004.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.14,0:03:16.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他立即引起了每个人的关注 因为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He had immediately got everybody's attention, because
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.46,0:03:18.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遭到碰撞的可能性非常的高 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the probability of impact was quite high.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.73,0:03:21.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上比任何一次撞击概率更高 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In fact it was higher than any impact probability
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.02,0:03:24.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比那时以前碰到过的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we had ever seen up until that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.99,0:03:31.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,施威卡特有一个以前现实生活中的例子 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Schweickart has a terrifying real life example of just how damaging
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.17,0:03:34.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就是一颗小行星造成的破坏 那要比阿波菲斯小得多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an impact from an asteroid, even smaller than Apophis, could be.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.27,0:03:44.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那是在1908年6月30日上午7:15 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}June 30th 1908, 7:15 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:55.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个物体 有半个足球场那么大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An object, half the size of a football field,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.44,0:03:59.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从空中以每小时34000英里砸下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}plunged down from space at around 34,000 miles per hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.39,0:04:02.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它的后面拖着一股火焰 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And produced a stream of fiery gas behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.06,0:04:06.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,几分钟里 火球进入了我们的大气层 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within minutes, the fireball entered our atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.41,0:04:10.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在西伯利亚通古斯加森林爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and violently exploded about Siberia's Tunguska forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.98,0:04:20.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,成为现代人类历史中地球上最大的爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It became the largest explosion on Earth in modern human history.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.47,0:04:24.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爆炸形成冲击波 在大半个罗得岛的范围内 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The blast parted waves, which torched 8 million trees
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.98,0:04:27.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,点燃了800万棵树木 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in an area over half the size of Rhode Island.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.32,0:04:32.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,幸运的是在那次爆炸中没有一人死亡 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fortunately no one died as a direct result of the explosion,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.87,0:04:35.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是因为那是一个人烟稀少的地区 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it was in a thinly populated area.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:40.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果那个小行星晚几个小时撞击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If that asteroid hit just a few hours later,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.01,0:04:43.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就不会是西伯利亚 就会是整个欧洲 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would not have hit Siberia, it would have hit over Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.53,0:04:48.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果那次在欧洲任何一个主要城市上空爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if that had exploded midair over any of the major cities of Europe,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.60,0:04:50.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会有一百万人死于灾难 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a million people would died like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.56,0:04:55.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在最近的一百年里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For the last hundred years,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.18,0:04:58.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,通古斯加爆炸笼罩在争论之中 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Tunguska explosion has been shrouded in controversy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.95,0:05:03.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,今天许多科学家同意是一颗小行星引起了爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today many scientists agree an asteroid cause the blast.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.44,0:05:08.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难以置信的是它没有撞击地面 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Incredibly, it never even impacted the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.38,0:05:13.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,准确地说 是在西伯利亚冰封的大地上空5英里的地方爆炸的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rather, it exploded five miles above Siberia's frozen ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.52,0:05:19.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,石质小行星在我们大气层是无法幸免的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A small stony asteroid can't survive the plaster of ours atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.80,0:05:21.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它进入大气层的下层 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it smacks into the lower atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.74,0:05:23.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每小时50000英里的速度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}doing about 50,000 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:25.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就象鸡蛋砸在混凝土上 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's like an egg smashing on the concrete.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.49,0:05:37.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,西伯利亚上空的爆炸释放的能量相当于15兆吨TNT \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The blast over Siberia released energy equivalent to 15 megatons of TNT,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.26,0:05:40.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比广岛原子弹大1000倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a thousand times greater than Hiroshima.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.13,0:05:44.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这发生在一个大城市 将会摧毁它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If this were to happen over a large city, it would annihilate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:59.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家把这些入侵者称为近地天体 NEOs \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists called these trespassers, Near Earth Objects, or NEOs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.84,0:06:03.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们是小行星和慧星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're asteroids and comets,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.22,0:06:07.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都是行星形成时的残留物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which are leftovers from the formation of the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:11.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,慧星在柯伊伯带的奥尔特云里移动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Comets move in the Oort Cloud in the Kuiper Belt,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.25,0:06:13.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,超过海王星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is beyond the planet Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.67,0:06:18.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星在木星和火星之间游荡 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Asteroids travel in a bend between Jupiter and Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.70,0:06:21.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但它们的轨道十分随意 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But their orbital trip isn't always routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.74,0:06:25.95,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数的小行星的轨道靠近火星和木星之间 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the asteroids orbit in a neat belt between Mars and Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.16,0:06:27.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们不担心那些 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we don't worry much about those.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:30.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但有一个跑出来 所有的物质和能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But when one gets away, and all that mass and energy
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.22,0:06:33.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会朝向地球 那时天文学家就会感到忧虑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is headed towards Earth, that's when the astronomers start to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.17,0:06:40.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,经常会有宇宙残留物脱离其轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Often times these cosmic remnants get bumped out of her orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.31,0:06:43.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,跑入与地球相碰的路径 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and head on a collision course with Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.85,0:06:49.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们地球厚厚的大气层会蒸发其中的大部分 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our planet's thick atmosphere vaporizes the vast majority of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.23,0:06:55.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而较大的物体会通过大气层造成撞击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But a larger object can knock through our atmosphere
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.24,0:06:57.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,甚至会撞击地面 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and actually impact the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.16,0:07:02.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你想回到宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you want to turn to the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.90,0:07:04.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,看一下会给我们带来死亡的影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and look at the forces that would have us dead,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.93,0:07:09.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星攻击是真的坏东西 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}asteroids striking are real and they're bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:12.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它以前发生过 将来还会发生 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's happened before, it will happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.09,0:07:17.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,6500万年前 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}65 million years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.52,0:07:22.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗小城市规模的小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an asteroid the size of a small city
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.75,0:07:25.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,从空中落下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}plummeted down from the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.87,0:07:30.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在犹卡坦半岛爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It exploded in the Yucatan peninsula
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.07,0:07:34.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在的齐克夏拉伯的墨西哥村庄 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}near the present day Mexican village of Chicxulub,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.44,0:07:38.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当量为一兆兆吨TNT \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the force of one hundred million megatons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.23,0:07:42.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这里是地球…投下…\NHere's the Earth… cast…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.14,0:07:46.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数十亿吨地壳进入大气层 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of tons of Earth's crust into the atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.08,0:07:50.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,覆盖了地球 遮蔽了阳光 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cloaking Earth, blocking out sunlight,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.80,0:07:52.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,淘汰了事物链的根基 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}knocking out the base of the food chain
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.67,0:07:55.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发出的冲击波拦腰折断生命之树 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and sending a wave of extinction across the tree of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.69,0:07:59.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这被认为是一次极度的撞击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It is believed the ferocious impact
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.95,0:08:03.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抛出的质量消灭了恐龙 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}contributed to the mass extinction of the dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.04,0:08:07.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们认为小行星是件坏事 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can think of asteroids as being bad things,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.34,0:08:11.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如果不是小行星 就不会有我们的今天 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but if it were not for an asteroid we wouldn't be here today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.25,0:08:14.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们哺乳动物的祖先靠着双脚奔跑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our mammal ancestors were running on their foot,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.76,0:08:17.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,试图避免成为暴龙的盘中餐 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trying to avoid being hors d'oeuvres for T-rex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.59,0:08:21.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,暴龙出局了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}T-rex gets taken out.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.97,0:08:26.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这打开了一个生态环境 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well this opened up an ecological niche,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.40,0:08:29.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让哺乳动物的祖先得到进化成为 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that allowed our mammal ancestors to evolve
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.79,0:08:32.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是更重要的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to something more ambitious than a rout
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.42,0:08:37.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,灵长类 人类是灵长类之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and outcomes the primates and among the primates we have people.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.53,0:08:42.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇宙陨石很有点讽刺性 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But ironically the very kind of cosmic boulder
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.49,0:08:44.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,为人类生存铺平了道路 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that paved the way for humans to exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.23,0:08:48.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能有一天也把我们从地球上抹去 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may one day wipe us off the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.96,0:09:00.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,1998年 国会敦促美国国家航空航天局探测所有的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1998 Congress urged NASA to detect all the Near Earth Objects
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.99,0:09:03.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,直径在半英里以上的近地天体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}over a half mile in diameter or more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.22,0:09:07.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他们的发现令人不安 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what they found was unsettling.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.28,0:09:11.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有超过850个近地天体在我们附近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Over 850 NEOs in our vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.54,0:09:15.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些小行星是太阳系里靠我们最近\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These asteroids are our closest
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.59,0:09:18.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和最危险的邻居 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and most dangerous neighbors in the solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.56,0:09:29.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,唐纳德·姚曼斯带领着美国国家航空航天局的喷气推进实验室里的近地天体项目组 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Donald Yeomans heads the NEO program at NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.51,0:09:31.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他和他的宇宙赏金猎人们\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He and his cosmic bounty hunters
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.41,0:09:34.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,搜索着埋伏在太阳系里的潜在杀手 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}search for potential killers lurking in our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.01,0:09:37.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把它们列入通缉目录里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and put them on their most wanted list.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.89,0:09:42.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发现这些近地天体有点象跟踪飓风 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Finding these Near Earth Objects is somewhat liken to tracking hurricanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.74,0:09:46.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,随着日复一日的追踪 会得到其轨道的较好的概念 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As you track it, day after day, you get a better idea of its orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.13,0:09:49.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就能预报其会到哪里 有多大 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you can predict where it's going, you have a better idea how large it is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.67,0:09:53.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,以及假如它撞击地球 会以什么样的速度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, if it should hit the Earth, with what sort of velocity.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.67,0:09:57.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,靠着望远技术 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}By using telescopic technologies
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.37,0:10:03.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,美国国家航空航天局的防卫监测已经探测到90%以上的疑似有害的近地天体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Spaceguard Survey has detected over 90% of all NEOs deemed harmful.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.91,0:10:07.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些令人恐惧的天体会撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These frightening objects could strike the Earth with the energy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.01,0:10:11.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其能量超过地球上现有的核武器 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}greater than all the nuclear weapons on our planet today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.40,0:10:16.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样的撞击会引发毁灭 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such an impact could trigger mass extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.52,0:10:18.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们无法预料数百 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We wouldn't expect one to hit about,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.82,0:10:21.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数千或者数百万年里会发生一次 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every several hundred,  thousand or millions of years,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.69,0:10:26.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但一旦发生 就会消灭不同的人种 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but if one did it, it could wipe out  different fraction of the population.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.01,0:10:30.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以是个概率很低但后果严重的事件 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So there are very low probability events but high consequence events.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.11,0:10:35.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果撞击地球就是全球性的事情 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If they hit the Earth they would have global effects.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:40.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,真的发生沉重的打击不仅会抹去大陆 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They not only would you wipe out a continent with really heavy shockwaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.84,0:10:43.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还会把陆地抛进大气层 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the ejected would be thrown up in the air
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.98,0:10:46.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然后掉下来覆盖地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and come down all around the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.24,0:10:50.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大气层温度会达到大约1000度…\Nthe atmosphere itself would get to a thousand degrees or so…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.57,0:10:53.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所有地面上的植被\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all the vegetation all over the world where that happens
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.79,0:10:56.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会瞬间燃烧 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would flash into flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.43,0:11:00.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,较小的物体也会引发灾难 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cataclysms could also occur with smaller objects,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:08.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以国会要求美国国家航空航天局定位所有直径500英尺的近地天体 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so Congress now asks NASA to locate all NEOs 500 feet in diameter,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.71,0:11:11.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象罗马大剧场那么宽 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as wide as the roman Colosseum.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.48,0:11:17.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大的天体会消灭首都甚至小的州 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An object that big could decimate a metropolitan area or even a small state.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.82,0:11:23.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家最担忧的不是已经发现的小行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what worries scientists most is not the asteroids they've discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.65,0:11:26.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是还没有被发现的那些 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but the ones they have not yet found.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.98,0:11:29.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那个 在给定的时间里还有大约2000个天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, at the given time there's about 2000 objects
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.62,0:11:32.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们还无法排除其对地球的影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for which we can't yet rule out an Earth impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.71,0:11:44.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,前宇航员施威卡特更进一步地看到了近地天体的威胁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Former astronaut Schweickart has taken the threat of NEOs one step further.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.13,0:11:46.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他来到国会前 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's up here before Congress
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.79,0:11:49.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,要求政府委派专员负责\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to request a special government agency be responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.97,0:11:52.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,保护公众 对付太空石块 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for protecting the public from space rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.42,0:11:57.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在我们已经具备技术终止\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today we have the technology to stop
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.78,0:12:04.03,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,近地天体在今后撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Near Earth Objects from impacting the Earth for the rest of history.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.13,0:12:06.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我的意思是 我们现在能够\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I mean, we can literally now
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.31,0:12:10.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始逐步局部地改造太阳系 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}begin to reshape the local solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.00,0:12:13.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样我们的生存机会就会得到提高 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that our survival is enhanced.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.49,0:12:18.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,问题是:我们会是或我们会步恐龙的后尘吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The question is: will we or will we go the way of the dinosaurs?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.63,0:12:30.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是施威卡特没有等待美国国家航空航天局或国会解决问题 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But Schweickart isn't waiting for NASA or Congress to solve the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.25,0:12:37.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他有自己的方案 在下一个小行星撞击时解救地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He has his own plans to save the planet from the next asteroid impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.92,0:12:50.88,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,难以相信地球已经幸存了45亿年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's hard to believe the Earth has survived over 4.5 billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.10,0:12:55.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,自从在地球幼年是发生过一次撞击后 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because since its infancy the planet has taken a beating.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.99,0:13:03.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象个拳击师 地球处在小行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like a boxer, our world is under constant assault
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.82,0:13:07.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,闯入地球轨道持续的打击下 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from asteroids that enter our orbit each year,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.92,0:13:11.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在将来 地球也会遭遇打击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but in the future Earth could be knocked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.02,0:13:17.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,前阿波罗9号宇航员拉塞尔·施威卡特\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Former Apollo 9 astronaut, Rusty Schweickart refuses
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:19.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拒绝小行星的威胁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be bullied by asteroids,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.53,0:13:23.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在他准备为地球对抗有害的小行星进行辩护 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and now he's ready to defend Earth against these harmful rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.95,0:13:27.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们发现这些近地天体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've discovered that there are these Near Earth Objects
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.80,0:13:29.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,时刻都在飞近我们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flying by us all the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.74,0:13:34.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们已经有了越来越多的能力来改造\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we've got more and more capability to modify our environment to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.97,0:13:36.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们的生存环境 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}enhance our survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.77,0:13:43.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,施威卡特特别关注编号为2004MN4的小行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schweickart is particularly concerned about an asteroid named 2004MN4,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.70,0:13:45.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,更熟悉的名字叫阿波菲斯 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}better known as Apophis.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.90,0:13:51.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个长着痘痘的石头 有近750英尺的直径 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This pockmarked rock, approximately 750 feet in diameter,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.65,0:13:54.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2004年掠过地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}swept near Earth in 2004.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.92,0:13:58.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在预计会再次危险地经过地球附近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now it's scheduled to pass dangerously close to our planet again,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:02.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会在2029年4月13日 星期五 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on Friday, the 13th in April 2029.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.75,0:14:05.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此在2029年…So in 2029…\NSo in 2029…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.82,0:14:08.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿波菲斯将会靠近我们 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Apophis will come closer to us
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.76,0:14:11.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比地球的同步轨道卫星更近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than our roam communication satellites orbiting the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.90,0:14:16.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它是如此的接近 适当的地方的人们将会肉眼看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It will be so close that people who are in the right place will be able to see
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.70,0:14:19.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿波菲斯来到地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Apophis go by the Earth with your naked eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.77,0:14:21.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你甚至可以闭上你的双眼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You won't even have to have binocular,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.64,0:14:24.65,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象那个小行星将会多么的近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's how close that asteroid is gonna come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.82,0:14:31.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2029年 阿波菲斯有99%的机会错开地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Apophis has an over 99% chance of missing the Earth in 2029,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.54,0:14:37.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是如果阿波菲斯在离地球精确的距离 18893英里的地方经过 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but if Apophis passes the Earth at a distance of exactly 18,893 miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:40.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,可能会通过一个引力眼 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it may pass through a gravitational keyhole,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.15,0:14:44.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一个太空的狭窄区域 有半英里宽 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a narrow region in space, a half mile wide.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.43,0:14:47.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果这发生 地球的引力会干扰阿波菲斯 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If this happens, the Earth's gravity could upset Apophis,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.92,0:14:49.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,改变它的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and change its trajectory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.81,0:14:53.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会引起它返回 在7年后撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It could cause it to return, and hit Earth seven years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.67,0:14:56.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2036年4月13日 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on April 13th, 2036.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.66,0:15:01.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球引力的作用 会征服它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gravitational effect of the Earth, would cause it to bend,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.02,0:15:08.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成阿波菲斯的轨道扩大到正好在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cause the Apophis' orbit to enlarge to precisely the size, which
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.66,0:15:12.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,7年后回到并撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seven years later it will come around and hit the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.63,0:15:20.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 阿波菲斯有1:45的机会 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At the present time, Apophis has 1 in 45.000 chance
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.53,0:15:23.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在2036年给地球致命的一击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of delivering a deadly blow in 2036.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.34,0:15:28.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而甚至这些机会都是科学家的打赌 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even these odds have scientists placing bets.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.15,0:15:34.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是一件已经知道可能是45分之一的机会的事情 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's one thing to know that there is maybe 1 chance on 45.000,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.95,0:15:37.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,将会撞击地球 但是你不会愿意去知晓 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it's gonna hit the Earth, but what you'd like to know is
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.56,0:15:40.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果是百分之一 十分之一 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if there is one chance in a hundred, if there is one chance in ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.48,0:15:44.34,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果就是百分之百将会撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if there is a probability one that it's gonna hit the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.68,0:15:55.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,施威卡特认为我们必须关注阿波菲斯 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schweickart believes we must regard Apophis
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.31,0:15:57.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就象对待其它自然灾害一样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as we would any natural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.57,0:16:02.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他甚至绘制了阿波菲斯可能撞击的地图 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's even mapped out where Apophis might strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.23,0:16:05.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你有撞击的数据 撞击的时间 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You have the date of the impact, the time of the impact,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.08,0:16:09.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,轨道的倾角 你就可以绘制地图了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the orbital inclination, and you can make a map.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.01,0:16:15.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那张地图表明 这就是我称之为的"冒险小路" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And what that map shows, is what I have called a "path of risk".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.57,0:16:17.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将给出越过地球的所有路经 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It goes all the way across the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.47,0:16:22.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我看到这 看到碰撞的高机会 我说…\Nand I look at this and I see a high probability of impact and I say…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.23,0:16:25.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,哇 你看 会撞击哪里？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Wow! You know, where might it hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.65,0:16:32.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,按照施威卡特的说法 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}According to Schweickart,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.41,0:16:36.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,阿波菲斯撞击点会沿着"冒险小路" \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Apophis could impact any point along this "path of risk".
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.82,0:16:39.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,开始在西西泊利亚 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It begins in Western Siberia,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.57,0:16:43.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,削过太平洋降下 在加利福尼亚附近 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}cuts across and down the Pacific Ocean, near California,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.56,0:16:48.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着它横穿美国中部 结束在西非 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then it traverses Central America and finishes in Western Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.58,0:16:53.70,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,施威卡特提出了一个阿波菲斯可能击中之地的令人恐惧的假设 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schweickart proposes a chilling scenario of where Apophis might strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.21,0:16:59.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星会在太平洋尽头的加利福尼亚海滩登陆 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The asteroid could land in the Pacific Ocean off the coast of California,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.20,0:17:03.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量超过一百万兆吨TNT \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with a force of over one million megatons of TNT.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.76,0:17:05.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样一个撞击会在水里造成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Such an impact would create
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.30,0:17:09.09,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,5英里宽 9000英尺深的弹坑 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a 5 mile wide, 9,000 foot deep crater in the water,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.27,0:17:11.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会引起海啸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which would unleash tsunamis,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.76,0:17:16.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,50英尺高的海浪将拍打海岸线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with reckless 50 foot waves would pound the coast line,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.23,0:17:18.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,造成不计其数的人员死亡 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}resulting in unimaginable human loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.20,0:17:25.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一颗1000英尺直径的小行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An asteroid a thousand feet in diameter,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.84,0:17:30.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撞击海洋不是件好事 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}having it hitting the ocean is not a good deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.08,0:17:36.20,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,上千亿美元的损失 事情就是这样 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hundreds of billions of dollars of damage. For something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.25,0:17:41.62,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,科学家目前做的事是靠技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists are presently working on technologies
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.72,0:17:44.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对这样的宇宙打击提前行动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to pre-empt such a cosmic strike.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.58,0:17:49.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一个想法是介入炸毁小行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One idea involves blowing up an asteroid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.50,0:17:55.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而感到会把问题搞得复杂化 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But some feel this could compound the problem,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.42,0:18:00.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,小行星碎成几大块替代它在地球的前面 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sending several chunks of the asteroid in our direction instead of just one.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.69,0:18:04.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此施威卡特的新主意\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Consequently, Schweickart's new mission
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.32,0:18:08.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是改变小行星可能撞击地球的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is to change the orbit of asteroids that could impact Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.94,0:18:12.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你想要做的是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What you wanna do is basically
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.21,0:18:15.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常非常细微地改变小行星的基本轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}change the asteroid's orbit very, very slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.00,0:18:21.44,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,把它的速度由每小时一万英里改变为一英里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Change its velocity by a ten thousand of a mile per hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.84,0:18:24.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这样它将与地球擦肩而过 不会撞击地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that it will miss the Earth instead of hitting it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.36,0:18:30.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,拉塞尔的同僚已经构思了太空船的概念设计 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rusty's colleagues have drafted a conceptual design
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.71,0:18:35.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,用来偏转小行星 独特的阿波菲斯 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a spacecraft that could deflect asteroids. Particularly Apophis.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.86,0:18:38.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它将把小行星拖离地球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One would tow armful asteroids away from Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:41.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不是象牛崽表演套牛那样套住小行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But instead of lassoing the rock like a bull at a Rodeo,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.06,0:18:46.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而是盘旋在小行星前面 用地球引力作为拖绳 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the tractor will hover in front of it, and use gravity as a tow line.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.27,0:18:50.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果你停在小行星前面足够长的时间 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you park in front of an asteroid for a long enough period of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:53.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,充分地靠近它 但不接触它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you stay close enough to it, but not touching it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.10,0:18:59.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就会增加它的速度 否则 如果你在它的背后停留 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're going to increase its velocity, or, if you park behind it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.44,0:19:03.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当它往前跑的时候 就会很细微地让它慢下来 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while it's moving along, you're going to slow it down very slightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.18,0:19:07.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以改变一颗小行星的轨道 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can change the orbit of an asteroid,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.37,0:19:10.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只要我们有足够的时间提前掌握它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we know about it far enough ahead of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.38,0:19:15.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尽管太空探测器已经在过去登陆过小行星 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Although a space probe has landed on an asteroid in the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.18,0:19:21.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,最具挑战性的想法是发射载人飞船 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most challenging idea is launching a manned mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.07,0:19:31.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,宇航员在登陆过的小行星上装上无线电传送器 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Once landing on the rock, astronauts could mount a radio transponder,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.05,0:19:33.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来跟踪它的行踪 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to track its whereabouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.30,0:19:37.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可以使用机器人前往小行星 进行登陆 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You could just use a robotic mission to go to an asteroid, and land,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.18,0:19:41.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,取得样本后返回 这并不困难 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}grab a sample and bring it back. That's not that difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.35,0:19:44.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而载人任务的好处是宇航员可以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What you gain by a man mission is they can
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.91,0:19:49.86,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对小行星表面感兴趣的地方作出反应 他们可以去这儿 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}react to interesting areas on the asteroid's surface. They could go here,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.99,0:19:55.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那儿 那儿 他们不必依靠远程导航 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there, there. And they wouldn't have to rely on remote navigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.40,0:19:59.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尼加拉瓜边境…\NNicaraguan border…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.88,0:20:04.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,施威卡特强调我们应该对小行星阿波菲斯保持高度警惕 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Schweickart insists we should remain on high alert regarding asteroid Apophis.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.63,0:20:08.39,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的想法已经让大家听到了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And his cause hasn't gone unheard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.06,0:20:13.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,目前联合国计划草拟一个条约 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now the United Nations plans to draft a treaty,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.41,0:20:15.53,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其中将包括由谁来负责\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which will include who will be responsible
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.63,0:20:18.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,偏转小行星杀手 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for deflecting killer asteroids.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.60,0:20:24.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,如果我们是如此地不负责任的话 那将真的是个犯罪 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That will be a real crime if we are so irresponsible,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.47,0:20:28.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即已经知道将要发生 而我们依然不作出反应 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}knowing that this is gonna happen, that we continue to do nothing about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.08,0:20:40.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过小行星和彗星不是唯一的来自太空深处的威胁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But asteroids and comets are not the only deep space threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.64,0:20:49.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球经历了上升以及…地球经历了下降 \NEarth has had its ups and… Earth has had its downs.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.62,0:20:55.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你永远不会知道围绕着下一个困境的是什么 会有多糟糕 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You never know what's gonna be around the next corner, and a lot of it is bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:02.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,星系的远处 银河的入侵者在活动 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In far of galaxies, galactic invaders are at work.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.70,0:21:05.92,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,渴望结束地球的生命 因为我们知道这一点 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Itching to end life on the planet, as we know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.34,0:21:11.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,每天三次奇异的闪光搏动横跨我们的天空 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Three times daily a strange flash pulsates across our sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.54,0:21:17.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比世界上所有的核武器总和强上数百倍 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's hundreds of times more powerful than the world's total nuclear armament.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.29,0:21:19.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而那不是人造的:\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it's not man-made:
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.89,0:21:22.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而当它足够靠近地球发生 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And if one happens close enough to Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.17,0:21:25.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会结束地球的生命 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it could end life on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.57,0:21:40.50,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,大多数人没有觉察到太空中潜在的危险 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most earthlings are unaware of the potential hazards in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.60,0:21:43.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但是目录很长而且在不断增长 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the list is long and growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.48,0:21:46.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下这个 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.08,0:21:52.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在我们的星系--银河系里 一颗巨大的恒星爆发 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Within our own galaxy, the Milky Way, a massive star explodes,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.28,0:21:59.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,抛出大量的致命能量冲击波来到我们的星球 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}sending a lethal burst of energy rocketing into our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.09,0:22:04.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是伽玛射线 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is a gamma ray burst,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.63,0:22:08.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,撼动宇宙最大的爆炸 源自宇宙大爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the biggest explosion to rock the Universe, since the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.00,0:22:14.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在城市和乡村\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the cities and countryside below
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.15,0:22:16.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对会发生什么没有任何警告 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there's no warning of what's about to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.60,0:22:22.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,接着 发生了撞击 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, it strikes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.77,0:22:28.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,相当于站在广岛一英里远的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be equivalent to standing one mile away from Hiroshima,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.52,0:22:30.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,地球上任何一个地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any place on the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.38,0:22:36.30,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不断冲击的射线烧烤着大气层的上部 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The pumped radiation cooks the upper atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.22,0:22:41.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,臭氧层被烧烤 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our ozone layer roasts.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.71,0:22:45.91,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在大气层里 人们被高于致命剂量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Across the atmosphere human beings burns to death from radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.01,0:22:48.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,100倍的射线灼烧致死 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hundred times the fatal dose.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.70,0:22:54.82,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,臭氧层的消失引起全球气温升高 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The disappearing ozone layer causes increase temperatures around the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.92,0:22:57.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引发龙卷风 海啸和飓风 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}triggering cyclones, tsunamis and hurricanes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.63,0:23:03.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,陆地上和海洋里的大部分生命被烧死 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most life on the surfaces of land and water incinerates.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.51,0:23:08.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这有点象科幻小说 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This may seem like science fiction,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.94,0:23:11.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而有可能发生 如果来自100光年外的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it could happen, if a gamma ray burst hit Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.08,0:23:14.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线爆发打击地球的话 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from 100 light years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.39,0:23:19.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线爆发是宇宙中最明亮的爆炸 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Gamma ray bursts are the brightest explosions in the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.86,0:23:21.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为是如此的遥远 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because they are so far away
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.57,0:23:23.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,还依然如此的耀眼 因此必然是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they are still so brilliant they must involve
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.93,0:23:25.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,蕴藏着巨大的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an enormous amount of power.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.90,0:23:27.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能量相当于太阳在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As much energy as the Sun will emit
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.84,0:23:30.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,整整十亿年里喷发的能量 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in its entire ten billion year life time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.76,0:23:38.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,作为一名年轻的研究者 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As a young student,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.03,0:23:43.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,斯坦·伍丝尔利总是喜欢象玩方块炸弹游戏一样做实验 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Stan Woosley always like the experiments that go "boom".
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.31,0:23:45.52,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 这个天体物理学家的工作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now, the work of this astrophysicist
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.62,0:23:47.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就跟小孩子玩游戏差不多 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is more than child's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.76,0:23:49.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他的星系探测之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He's one of the galactic detectives
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.68,0:23:51.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是试图揭示伽玛射线爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trying to uncover the mysteries
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.69,0:23:53.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,背后的秘密 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}behind gamma ray bursts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.13,0:23:56.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道宇宙中遍布着\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know there're many planets and many stars
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.45,0:23:58.58,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,许多行星和恒星 所以就有可能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}throughout the cosmos, so there may have been
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.68,0:24:02.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,有数不清的文明被伽玛射线爆发摧毁 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}countless civilizations that were destroyed by gamma ray burst.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.35,0:24:06.22,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这些奇特的射线波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These peculiar beam of radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.32,0:24:08.56,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是在1960年被发现的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were first spotted in the 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.56,0:24:13.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,起先大多数科学家认为伽玛射线爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At first most astronomers believe these gamma ray bursts
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.16,0:24:16.43,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,必定是存在于我们的星系 银河系里 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}must exist in our own galaxy, the Milky Way,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.63,0:24:18.41,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是因为它们是如此的明亮 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because they're so bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.50,0:24:22.45,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,对此有个说法 如果它们发生在银河系以外 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are reason for that, one was if they're outside the galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.55,0:24:24.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那么其能量几乎令人难以置信 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then the energy was almost unbelievable.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.85,0:24:30.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但在当时 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But at the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.07,0:24:32.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,即使是最强大的望远镜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even the most powerful telescopes
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.09,0:24:35.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,都无法确定它们的位置和距离 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}couldn't determine their location and distance
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.77,0:24:36.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这是因为爆发\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the burst
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.89,0:24:38.67,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只维持了短短的几秒钟\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lasted for a few seconds
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.77,0:24:40.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就消失了 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.88,0:24:43.72,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而接着天文学家想知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But then astronomers wondered
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.82,0:24:45.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它们的余辉是什么 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what about their afterglow?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.99,0:24:50.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,典型的宇宙爆发会留下一些发光的残余物 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cosmic explosions typically leave behind some luminous residue
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.86,0:24:54.27,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会持续数天或数周 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that sometimes lasts for days or weeks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.27,0:24:57.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在90年代后期 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In the late 1990s
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.09,0:25:00.18,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,装有改进的光学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}satellites used upgraded optics
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.28,0:25:01.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,和X射线探测器的人造卫星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and x-ray detectors
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.74,0:25:05.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,终于捕获到了伽玛射线爆发的余辉 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to finally capture a gamma ray bursts afterglow.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.76,0:25:11.26,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它变得清晰了 伽玛射线爆发实际上是…宇宙学的 \NIt became clear that gamma ray burst actually were… cosmological,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.36,0:25:13.66,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,是来自银河系外遥远的地方 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}coming from very far outside of our galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.76,0:25:17.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,来自数百万和数十亿光年以外 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from millions and billions of light years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.49,0:25:20.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那意味着其能量必定是大的无法估量的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that meant their energy had to truly be astronomical.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.63,0:25:26.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你知道这伽玛射线爆发是\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You get some idea of how incredibly bright
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.73,0:25:28.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,多么地难以置信的明亮…\Na gamma ray burst is…
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.24,0:25:31.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以用这个相对暗淡的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We could represent the brightness of our Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.14,0:25:33.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,发光二极管来代表太阳的亮度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by this relatively dim led
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.00,0:25:36.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,同时我们可以用在我身后的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we can represent the brightness of the gamma ray burst
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.71,0:25:38.77,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,非常非常强烈的探照灯来代表\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the very very intense searchlight
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.87,0:25:40.51,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线爆发的亮度 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that's behind me,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.61,0:25:42.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,亮得无法相信 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and then incredibly bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.49,0:25:45.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个对比令人遗憾 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unfortunately with this comparison,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.11,0:25:47.35,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,探照灯的光度几乎还不足以\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the searchlight is not nearly bright enough
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.45,0:25:49.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,充分代表伽玛射线爆发 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to represent fully the gamma ray burst
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.27,0:25:52.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,事实上我们需要1000亿个这样的探照灯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and in fact we'd need a hundred billion such searchlights
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.79,0:25:54.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才够得上进行对比 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to have an adequate comparison.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.61,0:25:57.29,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,伽玛射线爆发相当于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The gamma ray burst is equivalent
