Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.43,0:39:21.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够感觉到它 通过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can feel what it is, we feel that through
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.56,0:39:25.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它在宇宙间对引力的作用感觉到它 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its effects on the gravitational  behavior of the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.86,0:39:29.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这个房间里可能有暗能量 在椅子下…\NThere could be some dark energy in this room, under the chair…
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.35,0:39:32.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,只有真正在大的宇宙尺度下\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's only when you look at its properties
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.36,0:39:35.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,才能看到它的性质 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on really big cosmological length scales,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.36,0:39:37.80,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,数十亿光年的跨度 你开始看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}billions of light-years across, that you start to see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.90,0:39:41.08,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,聚集的暗能量的影响 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the accumulated effects of the dark energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.50,0:39:44.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它造成物体相互推开 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It causes things to be pushed farther away from each other
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.10,0:39:48.10,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,引起宇宙的膨胀 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and contributes to the expansion of the Universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.71,0:39:49.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,并且加快步伐 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it quicken in pace.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.91,0:39:57.21,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,爱德温·哈勃 后来以他的名字命名哈勃望远镜 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Edwin Hubble, whom the Hubble telescope is named after,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.41,0:40:01.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,早在1920年第一个发现宇宙在膨胀 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}first discovered the Universe is expanding back in the 1920s.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.41,0:40:04.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,然而直到1998年 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it wasn't until the 1998
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.71,0:40:07.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,当时一支精锐科学家团队衡量这种扩张\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when a crack team of scientists measured that this expansion
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.91,0:40:10.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,象失控的火车 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is moving like a runaway train.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.61,0:40:16.61,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,恰当的比喻是宇宙\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A nice analogy is to imagine that the Universe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.11,0:40:19.97,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在三维空间里象一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are three-dimensional spaces like the surface of a
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.07,0:40:21.71,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我正在吹起的橡皮球的表面 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}rubber balloon that I'm blowing up.
